The paper proposes a dynamic map of knowledge generated from Wikipedia pages and the Web URLs contained therein, which involves constructing a semantic network of the most relevant pages in Wikipedia related to a search term. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Information Retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category, which deals with the organization, storage, retrieval, and search of information resources. Additionally, the paper mentions the importance of article quality, which suggests that it may also belong to the Computational Linguistics (cs.CL) sub-category, which deals with the study of natural language processing and understanding. The paper also mentions the use of visual temporal maps, which suggests that it may belong to the Digital Libraries (cs.DL) sub-category, which deals with the management and dissemination of digital information. Furthermore, the paper mentions the use of bidirectional link structures and network centrality, which suggests that it may also belong to the Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) sub-category, which deals with the analysis and modeling of social and information networks. Finally, the paper mentions the use of updates and changes, which suggests that it may also belong to the Databases (cs.DB) sub-category, which deals with the management and analysis of large-scale data sets.
